1
00:00:15,333 --> 00:00:17,500
They haven't overtaken
the truck yet.

2
00:00:17,633 --> 00:00:21,467
If Red's car is here,
but Lucho's car is not...

3
00:00:21,600 --> 00:00:24,633
that means they have Red
in the car.

4
00:00:24,767 --> 00:00:27,200
- What's the matter, Red?
- Yen, the brake is not working.

5
00:00:27,333 --> 00:00:28,467
What are we going to do?

6
00:00:28,600 --> 00:00:30,367
I have to crash this somewhere.

7
00:00:30,500 --> 00:00:31,367
No, Red.

8
00:00:31,500 --> 00:00:33,067
Yen, this is the only way.

9
00:00:33,200 --> 00:00:34,533
What about you?

10
00:00:34,700 --> 00:00:36,300
When I say jump,
you have to jump.

11
00:00:36,433 --> 00:00:37,333
Red, no!

12
00:00:37,467 --> 00:00:39,400
- We don't have a choice!
- No, Red!

13
00:00:39,533 --> 00:00:40,667
- One!
- Red, no!

14
00:00:40,800 --> 00:00:41,900
Two!

15
00:00:42,033 --> 00:00:43,233
Three!

16
00:00:43,367 --> 00:00:44,333
Go!

17
00:00:54,300 --> 00:00:57,067
Lucho, we can't lose them.

18
00:00:57,200 --> 00:00:59,900
Red can't take Yenyen with him.

19
00:01:00,033 --> 00:01:01,800
I can't lose my daughter!

20
00:01:01,933 --> 00:01:04,433
Yes. We'll find her.

21
00:01:04,567 --> 00:01:05,867
One!

22
00:01:07,300 --> 00:01:09,567
- Red, no!
- Two!

23
00:01:09,733 --> 00:01:10,700
Three!

24
00:01:12,400 --> 00:01:13,633
He's not answering.

25
00:01:13,767 --> 00:01:15,267
What if my suspicion is correct?

26
00:01:15,400 --> 00:01:18,367
If you have to talk to Eden,
do so.

27
00:01:18,500 --> 00:01:20,400
I just want to make sure
that Red is safe.

28
00:01:20,533 --> 00:01:22,200
Rina, that's impossible!

29
00:01:22,333 --> 00:01:23,567
I can't talk to Eden.

30
00:01:23,700 --> 00:01:25,667
Do you want me to end up
in jail?

31
00:01:25,800 --> 00:01:28,133
Red, wake up!

32
00:01:28,267 --> 00:01:29,867
You promised we'd never give up.

33
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:32,233
Why are you giving up?

34
00:01:32,367 --> 00:01:35,133
Emma just told me
that Red had left the house.

35
00:01:35,267 --> 00:01:36,367
He's not here.

36
00:01:36,500 --> 00:01:40,967
I feel that he went
to Lucho's house to see Eden.

37
00:01:41,133 --> 00:01:42,233
That's their car!

38
00:01:43,700 --> 00:01:44,867
This is all your fault!

39
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:46,000
Rina, why are you blaming me?

40
00:01:46,133 --> 00:01:47,400
Isn't this your plan?

41
00:01:47,533 --> 00:01:50,467
You told me
to cut Lucho's brake line.

42
00:01:50,600 --> 00:01:53,467
Don't raise your voice at me,
Zandro.

43
00:01:53,600 --> 00:01:55,333
Hello? I'm his father.

44
00:01:56,667 --> 00:01:58,267
What?

45
00:01:58,400 --> 00:01:59,533
What hospital?

46
00:01:59,667 --> 00:02:02,100
I'll be straight
and firm with you, okay?

47
00:02:02,233 --> 00:02:05,133
She and the other patient
are still in critical condition.

48
00:02:05,267 --> 00:02:08,300
We still need to observe them
for the next 24 hours.

49
00:02:08,433 --> 00:02:11,500
My daughter will wake up, right?

50
00:02:11,633 --> 00:02:14,300
I cannot promise anything yet.

51
00:02:14,467 --> 00:02:17,833
But what I can promise
is we will do our best for them.

52
00:02:17,967 --> 00:02:19,933
As of now,
we've done everything we could.

53
00:02:20,067 --> 00:02:23,567
All we can do now is hope
and pray they'll improve, okay?

54
00:02:23,700 --> 00:02:24,667
Please excuse me.

55
00:02:24,800 --> 00:02:27,000
Doc, please do everything
you can to help her.

56
00:02:29,167 --> 00:02:31,833
Victor, our son.

57
00:02:31,967 --> 00:02:33,133
My Red.

58
00:02:34,567 --> 00:02:36,733
- Rina.
- You!

59
00:02:37,867 --> 00:02:41,167
This is all your son's fault!

60
00:02:42,333 --> 00:02:44,167
You're to blame!

61
00:02:44,300 --> 00:02:46,533
Because you're a pest!

62
00:02:46,667 --> 00:02:48,233
You're the root
of every misfortune!

63
00:02:48,400 --> 00:02:50,000
You killed my son before!

64
00:02:50,133 --> 00:02:52,467
And now Red!

65
00:02:52,600 --> 00:02:55,900
I wish they never met!

66
00:02:56,033 --> 00:02:59,100
If you have regrets, I do, too!

67
00:02:59,233 --> 00:03:03,000
I will never care
about your daughter!

68
00:03:03,133 --> 00:03:05,367
I'm so tired, Rina!

69
00:03:05,500 --> 00:03:07,700
But I want to hurt you!

70
00:03:07,833 --> 00:03:09,767
I want to kill you!

71
00:03:09,900 --> 00:03:11,033
I want to kill you!

72
00:03:11,167 --> 00:03:14,967
But it won't help
my daughter's condition!

73
00:03:15,100 --> 00:03:19,333
Rina, I just want
to be with my daughter.

74
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:22,333
But you ruined everything!

75
00:03:22,500 --> 00:03:27,667
You take my daughter away
from me again and again!

76
00:03:27,800 --> 00:03:31,333
If there's anyone to blame
for all of this, it's you!

77
00:03:31,467 --> 00:03:33,967
All because
of your selfish reasons!

78
00:03:34,100 --> 00:03:35,700
I'm not done with you, Amanda.

79
00:03:35,833 --> 00:03:38,967
Because I will never
forgive you!

80
00:03:39,100 --> 00:03:42,500
And if this is karma,
then you deserve it!

81
00:03:42,633 --> 00:03:45,333
Just keep my son out of it!

82
00:03:45,467 --> 00:03:46,600
If she's going to die,

83
00:03:46,733 --> 00:03:49,067
she better not take my son
with her!

84
00:03:49,200 --> 00:03:51,233
She can go straight to hell!

85
00:03:51,367 --> 00:03:52,800
You're so evil!

86
00:03:52,933 --> 00:03:54,000
You're a horrible person!

87
00:04:07,567 --> 00:04:10,633
I heard these two are lovers.

88
00:04:10,767 --> 00:04:13,100
But their families
hate each other.

89
00:04:13,233 --> 00:04:15,000
That's why they ran away.

90
00:04:16,233 --> 00:04:18,667
And this is what happened.
They got into an accident.

91
00:04:18,800 --> 00:04:21,567
Shocks.
It's like Romeo and Juliet.

92
00:04:21,700 --> 00:04:23,967
Maybe they love each other
so much.

93
00:04:24,100 --> 00:04:26,500
That's why they did everything
to fight for it.

94
00:04:31,267 --> 00:04:32,667
- You're so evil!
- How dare you!

95
00:04:32,800 --> 00:04:33,967
Stop it. Rina! Rina, stop!

96
00:04:34,100 --> 00:04:36,000
- Rina!
- That's enough!

97
00:04:37,333 --> 00:04:39,367
That's enough!
Don't fight in here!

98
00:04:39,500 --> 00:04:40,567
You can't make a scene here.

99
00:04:40,700 --> 00:04:41,467
- You have to stop.
- She's the one

100
00:04:41,600 --> 00:04:42,933
who's making a scene!

101
00:04:43,067 --> 00:04:43,933
You're a monster!

102
00:04:44,067 --> 00:04:45,567
You're evil!

103
00:04:47,100 --> 00:04:48,567
Let her go!

104
00:04:48,700 --> 00:04:50,567
Let your wife go!
You want to hurt me?

105
00:04:50,700 --> 00:04:53,500
No! It's all your fault, Amanda.

106
00:04:53,633 --> 00:04:56,433
You're to blame for all of this!

107
00:04:56,567 --> 00:04:58,100
This is all your fault!

108
00:04:58,233 --> 00:04:59,200
You better let her go!

109
00:04:59,333 --> 00:05:00,600
- That's all you can do!
- You better let her go!

110
00:05:00,767 --> 00:05:01,767
Admit that it's all your fault!

111
00:05:01,900 --> 00:05:03,500
Let your wife go!

112
00:05:03,633 --> 00:05:05,100
This is all your fault!

113
00:05:05,233 --> 00:05:06,667
- Stop it! That's enough!
- You want to kill me?

114
00:05:06,800 --> 00:05:08,633
- Yes!
- Do you want to kill me

115
00:05:08,767 --> 00:05:10,600
in exchange for your son's life?

116
00:05:10,733 --> 00:05:12,700
Your daughter
is not coming back to you!

117
00:05:12,833 --> 00:05:14,800
Do it!

118
00:05:14,933 --> 00:05:16,900
But not my daughter!

119
00:05:17,033 --> 00:05:19,333
Keep her out of this!

120
00:05:19,467 --> 00:05:22,333
Do you understand?
Not my daughter!

121
00:05:22,467 --> 00:05:23,533
Leave us alone!

122
00:05:23,667 --> 00:05:24,633
Make her go away.

123
00:05:24,767 --> 00:05:27,233
- Get her out of here!
- That's enough!

124
00:05:27,367 --> 00:05:28,967
I can buy this hospital!

125
00:05:29,100 --> 00:05:30,767
And I can also buy you!

126
00:05:30,900 --> 00:05:32,100
That's enough!

127
00:05:32,233 --> 00:05:34,067
This is not helping!

128
00:05:34,200 --> 00:05:35,833
What are you doing?

129
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:37,400
Victor!

130
00:05:37,533 --> 00:05:38,600
Get your wife out of here!

131
00:05:38,733 --> 00:05:41,400
- Get out of here!
- This is not over yet, Amanda.

132
00:05:41,533 --> 00:05:43,533
- This is not over!
- It's over!

133
00:05:43,667 --> 00:05:46,133
This is not over
until I forgive you!

134
00:05:46,267 --> 00:05:48,067
- Remember that!
- Let her go.

135
00:05:48,200 --> 00:05:49,067
Let your wife go!

136
00:05:49,200 --> 00:05:50,567
Come on!

137
00:05:52,133 --> 00:05:53,333
Nothing to do with you!

138
00:05:53,467 --> 00:05:54,867
Excuse me.

139
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:56,000
I just came here to inform you

140
00:05:56,133 --> 00:05:58,400
that we're trying to revive
both of your kids.

141
00:05:59,433 --> 00:06:00,633
Okay?

142
00:06:00,767 --> 00:06:02,000
Please keep quiet

143
00:06:02,133 --> 00:06:03,233
while we're trying
to do our work.

144
00:06:03,367 --> 00:06:04,200
We'll try to revive them.

145
00:06:04,333 --> 00:06:06,433
Then we'll update you
as soon as we can.

146
00:06:06,567 --> 00:06:07,567
Thank you.

147
00:06:13,667 --> 00:06:14,867
Lucho.

148
00:06:18,600 --> 00:06:19,733
Don't engage with her anymore.

149
00:06:21,533 --> 00:06:23,933
You've said everything
you wanted to say.

150
00:06:24,067 --> 00:06:25,933
You got all your emotions out.

151
00:06:28,233 --> 00:06:29,667
Eden is all that matters now.

152
00:06:29,800 --> 00:06:31,467
We should focus on her. Okay?

153
00:06:45,033 --> 00:06:46,000
My god!

154
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:10,433
My God, what's going on?

155
00:07:10,567 --> 00:07:11,700
Lucho.

156
00:07:19,567 --> 00:07:22,200
Victor, our son.

157
00:07:32,433 --> 00:07:33,467
Where am I?

158
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:40,000
Yen!

159
00:07:47,867 --> 00:07:49,467
- Red?
- Yen.

160
00:07:49,600 --> 00:07:50,867
- Red!
- Yen!

161
00:07:53,733 --> 00:07:54,667
Red.

162
00:08:00,667 --> 00:08:02,367
Red, I'm happy to see you here.

163
00:08:03,700 --> 00:08:06,267
I'm happy that I can touch you
and hug you.

164
00:08:07,667 --> 00:08:09,567
Yen, like I promised you.

165
00:08:10,800 --> 00:08:12,000
We're staying on this island.

166
00:08:14,100 --> 00:08:17,900
We'll stay
where everything started.

167
00:08:20,400 --> 00:08:25,133
Yen, we're free here.

168
00:08:27,933 --> 00:08:29,433
We're free to love.

169
00:08:31,300 --> 00:08:33,233
We're free to love each other.

170
00:08:36,167 --> 00:08:37,400
And I promise you...

171
00:08:40,433 --> 00:08:41,767
Yen, I promise you,

172
00:08:43,267 --> 00:08:44,500
I won't let go of you.

173
00:08:49,600 --> 00:08:51,633
Red, I'm happy
that I can touch you.

174
00:08:51,767 --> 00:08:53,567
I don't ever want to let you go.

175
00:08:55,700 --> 00:08:58,467
But what about the people
we love?

176
00:08:58,600 --> 00:09:00,367
What about my mom?

177
00:09:00,500 --> 00:09:02,533
Aunt Dindi?

178
00:09:02,667 --> 00:09:05,367
Your mom and your dad?

179
00:09:05,500 --> 00:09:08,667
I'm sure they'll be hurt
when we're gone.

180
00:09:10,033 --> 00:09:12,433
Yen, if we decide to return,

181
00:09:12,567 --> 00:09:14,800
we'll go back
to how it used to be.

182
00:09:14,933 --> 00:09:16,733
They won't accept
our relationship.

183
00:09:18,500 --> 00:09:20,467
But I don't want to hurt them,
Red.

184
00:09:22,133 --> 00:09:24,833
Even if it's hard,
even if it's painful...

185
00:09:26,467 --> 00:09:28,100
we should go back.

186
00:09:29,633 --> 00:09:31,833
We have to face our destiny.

187
00:09:32,867 --> 00:09:35,967
We have to accept our fate.

188
00:09:37,133 --> 00:09:38,133
Okay?

189
00:09:40,333 --> 00:09:42,567
As long as we're together,

190
00:09:43,667 --> 00:09:45,200
we can overcome everything.

191
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:51,233
Because our love...

192
00:09:52,967 --> 00:09:55,767
is our weapon

193
00:09:55,900 --> 00:09:59,600
to whatever life may throw
at us.

194
00:10:02,533 --> 00:10:03,800
I trust you.

195
00:10:30,533 --> 00:10:32,933
My God, I'm begging you.

196
00:10:33,067 --> 00:10:36,133
Please don't take my daughter
away from me yet.

197
00:10:39,400 --> 00:10:42,700
If I have to bargain with you,
I will.

198
00:10:42,833 --> 00:10:44,467
Just take my life away

199
00:10:44,600 --> 00:10:46,300
in exchange
for my daughter's life.

200
00:10:46,433 --> 00:10:48,267
Not her, please.

201
00:10:48,400 --> 00:10:49,633
Not my child.

202
00:10:49,767 --> 00:10:50,800
She's still young.

203
00:10:50,933 --> 00:10:53,300
She still has a future
ahead of her.

204
00:10:56,200 --> 00:10:58,033
My God.

205
00:11:01,333 --> 00:11:03,767
Please, forgive me.

206
00:11:05,333 --> 00:11:09,900
I know it's my fault.

207
00:11:11,033 --> 00:11:12,200
God forgive me,

208
00:11:12,333 --> 00:11:16,700
but I'd rather see you lose
that child than see the result

209
00:11:16,833 --> 00:11:20,367
of the biggest mistake
you've ever made!

210
00:11:28,000 --> 00:11:29,833
It's all my fault.

211
00:11:31,767 --> 00:11:34,500
Because I let hatred
get the better of me.

212
00:11:34,633 --> 00:11:37,233
Because I wanted
to take revenge.

213
00:11:38,600 --> 00:11:42,500
Mom, can you love
the people I love?

214
00:11:43,833 --> 00:11:44,833
If you love me,

215
00:11:44,967 --> 00:11:48,867
you will allow me
to live my life as I want.

216
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:52,567
He and his family bring nothing
but trouble to our life!

217
00:11:54,033 --> 00:11:56,667
Now, if you won't change
your mind,

218
00:11:57,767 --> 00:12:00,433
you won't get out of this room
too.

219
00:12:00,567 --> 00:12:01,667
Mom, what are you going to do?

220
00:12:02,733 --> 00:12:03,733
Mom!

221
00:12:06,233 --> 00:12:10,800
And now my daughter is suffering
because of what I've done.

222
00:12:10,933 --> 00:12:14,733
My God, please, forgive me.

223
00:12:16,633 --> 00:12:18,433
Mom, we're leaving because...

224
00:12:18,567 --> 00:12:20,033
we don't want to hurt you.

225
00:12:20,167 --> 00:12:23,233
We've decided to leave
so we can all have peace.

226
00:12:23,367 --> 00:12:27,167
Mom, we'll fulfill our dream
of having our own family.

227
00:12:27,300 --> 00:12:29,133
- No!
- Mom, just let us go.

228
00:12:29,267 --> 00:12:30,567
You're not going to get married!

229
00:12:30,700 --> 00:12:32,567
We're getting married
whether you like it or not.

230
00:12:32,700 --> 00:12:35,867
We'll all die here
before you can get married!

231
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:37,167
- Yen, let's go.
- Mom, let go of me.

232
00:12:40,033 --> 00:12:42,700
Please, forgive me.

233
00:12:42,833 --> 00:12:45,433
I'm begging you.

234
00:12:45,567 --> 00:12:47,500
Please, don't take my daughter
from me.

235
00:12:56,133 --> 00:12:57,967
I will change my ways.

236
00:12:59,700 --> 00:13:01,367
I will fix my life.

237
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:05,667
I will give her
everything Eden wants.

238
00:13:05,800 --> 00:13:08,533
I don't want to lose her.

239
00:13:11,233 --> 00:13:14,500
I will let go of the hatred
in my heart.

240
00:13:16,433 --> 00:13:18,667
I will forget my hatred
for Rina.

241
00:13:18,800 --> 00:13:22,933
Everything, God.

242
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:26,633
I will surrender everything.

243
00:13:26,767 --> 00:13:29,400
I will surrender everything,
oh, God.

244
00:13:29,533 --> 00:13:31,800
Please, don't take my daughter
from me.

245
00:13:31,933 --> 00:13:34,433
I'm begging you.

246
00:13:36,900 --> 00:13:40,467
Please!

247
00:13:40,600 --> 00:13:43,100
Please, heal my daughter.

248
00:13:43,233 --> 00:13:45,767
I'm begging you.

249
00:13:50,367 --> 00:13:52,167
God, please.

250
00:14:14,467 --> 00:14:16,733
Victor. What's going on, Victor?

251
00:14:16,867 --> 00:14:18,367
Is it going to happen again?

252
00:14:18,500 --> 00:14:20,067
Are we going to lose
another child?

253
00:14:20,200 --> 00:14:21,800
Victor, I can't bear it!

254
00:14:24,667 --> 00:14:27,867
You should have thought of that
when we still have Red.

255
00:14:29,167 --> 00:14:32,267
If only you had let go
of your hatred and revenge.

256
00:14:32,400 --> 00:14:34,333
Your war with Amanda
would have ended

257
00:14:34,467 --> 00:14:36,467
a long time now.

258
00:14:38,567 --> 00:14:40,767
Our son wouldn't be fighting
for his life right now.

259
00:14:43,033 --> 00:14:44,467
I promise, Red.

260
00:14:46,200 --> 00:14:49,300
We'll be together until the end.

261
00:15:30,600 --> 00:15:33,533
If there's anyone
to blame here, Rina,

262
00:15:33,667 --> 00:15:35,200
it's you...

263
00:15:35,367 --> 00:15:36,333
us.

264
00:15:37,400 --> 00:15:40,167
So we have to accept
whatever happens to Red.

265
00:15:40,300 --> 00:15:41,967
No, I can't let that happen!

266
00:15:42,100 --> 00:15:43,833
I can't let anything happen
to our son!

267
00:15:43,967 --> 00:15:45,667
If someone deserves to die here,

268
00:15:45,800 --> 00:15:48,467
it's Amanda's daughter,
not our son!

269
00:16:21,100 --> 00:16:22,233
Red?

270
00:16:40,367 --> 00:16:41,400
Red!

271
00:16:51,233 --> 00:16:53,567
Amanda, good news!

272
00:16:53,700 --> 00:16:54,900
They've revived Eden.

273
00:16:56,467 --> 00:16:57,800
Thank God.

274
00:16:59,100 --> 00:17:01,000
He still answered my prayers.

275
00:17:04,033 --> 00:17:05,300
- Hi, good evening.
- Doctor.

276
00:17:05,433 --> 00:17:07,033
Bet you've seen your kids
right now.

277
00:17:08,200 --> 00:17:11,800
The good news,
their vital signs are improving.

278
00:17:11,933 --> 00:17:13,267
Thank you.

279
00:17:13,400 --> 00:17:16,533
If this keeps up, we can send
them to their private rooms.

280
00:17:16,700 --> 00:17:17,667
Okay?

281
00:17:18,967 --> 00:17:22,533
Also, to share,
it's like a miracle happened.

282
00:17:22,667 --> 00:17:24,567
They both flatlined.

283
00:17:24,700 --> 00:17:27,267
And they both got revived.

284
00:17:27,400 --> 00:17:30,900
I can't explain it.
It's as if they are connected.

285
00:17:31,167 --> 00:17:32,033
So...

286
00:17:32,167 --> 00:17:35,100
at least this is a God send
for you, guys.

287
00:17:35,233 --> 00:17:37,700
Doctor,
can I see my daughter now?

288
00:17:37,833 --> 00:17:39,500
Can I go to her now?

289
00:17:39,633 --> 00:17:40,667
Yes, sure.

290
00:17:40,800 --> 00:17:41,767
Why not?

291
00:17:41,900 --> 00:17:42,800
You'll see them now?

292
00:17:42,933 --> 00:17:43,867
- Yes, yes.
- Okay.

293
00:17:44,000 --> 00:17:45,300
Doctor, can we see our son too?

294
00:17:45,433 --> 00:17:46,733
We want to go inside too.

295
00:17:46,867 --> 00:17:49,067
One at a time, if it's okay.

296
00:18:27,167 --> 00:18:28,200
Zandro...

297
00:18:29,533 --> 00:18:31,167
stop looking for Red now.

298
00:18:31,300 --> 00:18:33,333
Because you won't be able
to find him.

299
00:18:33,467 --> 00:18:36,800
He's in the hospital. And thank
your stars that my son is alive!

300
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:41,333
Rina, why are you blaming me?

301
00:18:41,467 --> 00:18:44,200
I just did
what you asked me to do!

302
00:18:44,333 --> 00:18:46,067
I didn't know
Red would go there.

303
00:18:47,367 --> 00:18:50,867
Please, Zandro. I'm so tired
of arguing with you.

304
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:53,800
You always mess things up
for me!

305
00:18:56,100 --> 00:18:58,367
Rina, I didn't mess up.

306
00:18:58,500 --> 00:19:00,233
You didn't get to stop Red
from leaving.

307
00:19:01,367 --> 00:19:03,600
All your evil plans
against Amanda

308
00:19:03,733 --> 00:19:05,867
have backfired on you!

309
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:07,567
And now you're blaming me
for it?

310
00:19:08,600 --> 00:19:12,467
Zandro, please. Just make sure
the police won't find you.

311
00:19:12,600 --> 00:19:14,333
Go into hiding.

312
00:19:14,467 --> 00:19:18,033
And don't you ever rat me out!

313
00:19:19,400 --> 00:19:20,633
Who are you talking to?

314
00:19:22,800 --> 00:19:23,900
Who are you talking to?

315
00:19:28,400 --> 00:19:30,767
I ordered something online.

316
00:19:30,933 --> 00:19:36,867
They called me
because of what I had reserved.

317
00:19:37,000 --> 00:19:38,867
I told them to call me
some other time.

318
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:39,967
I'm busy now.

319
00:19:41,600 --> 00:19:43,567
Are you prioritizing that
over our son?

320
00:19:50,833 --> 00:19:51,833
Eden.

321
00:19:56,233 --> 00:20:01,533
Eden,
I don't wish for anything else

322
00:20:01,700 --> 00:20:03,333
but to be with you.

323
00:20:09,500 --> 00:20:11,967
I just want to be a mother
to you again.

324
00:20:18,200 --> 00:20:20,333
I want to tend
to your every need.

325
00:20:25,100 --> 00:20:26,800
I just want to take care of you.

326
00:20:33,533 --> 00:20:35,933
They took that away from me
for a long time.

327
00:20:41,567 --> 00:20:44,100
Why is it so hard to get?

328
00:20:46,767 --> 00:20:48,567
Why can't they let me have it?

329
00:20:51,500 --> 00:20:55,133
Don't I deserve your love?

330
00:21:01,200 --> 00:21:02,400
I'm asking you

331
00:21:02,533 --> 00:21:04,867
because I might not be deserving
of your love.

332
00:21:08,767 --> 00:21:11,067
That's why you chose Red
over me.

333
00:21:15,467 --> 00:21:19,200
Eden, please forgive me
for everything that I've done.

334
00:21:22,967 --> 00:21:24,667
Because of me...

335
00:21:26,533 --> 00:21:32,133
because of my anger
and obsession to get revenge,

336
00:21:32,267 --> 00:21:34,867
I put your life in danger.

337
00:21:41,100 --> 00:21:44,433
Rina might be right
that this is all my fault.

338
00:21:47,433 --> 00:21:48,867
Dindi was right.

339
00:21:49,000 --> 00:21:53,433
I shouldn't have gotten
between you and Red.

340
00:22:15,300 --> 00:22:17,167
The investigators
had informed me.

341
00:22:17,300 --> 00:22:19,767
They found out someone had cut
the car's brake line,

342
00:22:21,000 --> 00:22:23,867
which caused their accident.

343
00:22:24,000 --> 00:22:26,167
You were the target, Amanda.

344
00:22:26,300 --> 00:22:27,967
The kids just got involved.

345
00:22:28,100 --> 00:22:30,067
I asked for the footage.

346
00:22:30,200 --> 00:22:32,867
This is the answer
to all your questions.

347
00:22:33,000 --> 00:22:34,467
It's Zandro.

348
00:22:34,600 --> 00:22:37,167
How many times
did Rina abandon you?

349
00:22:38,200 --> 00:22:39,867
Do you think
she won't do it again?

350
00:22:40,900 --> 00:22:42,700
Your sister is just using you.

351
00:22:44,233 --> 00:22:47,867
Are you going to let her
get away with this?
